title: '"Reduced tax rate for non-profit organisations: the surpluses that are not invested or allocated to reach the entity’s “worthy purpose” are taxed at a reduced CIT rate of 20% rather than the standard CIT rate. The rationale for this preferential tax treatment is weak."'
pid: 0c6a9d48-5f23-4a89-afb0-9f560d7a9d3d
